Done. What was wrong and what was fixed:

  Root cause: tree-sitter.wasm (the main WebAssembly binary for the parser runtime) was never copied from node_modules/web-tree-sitter/ into public/tree-sitter/. When the renderer
   called Parser.init(), it fetched tree-sitter/tree-sitter.wasm — Vite found no matching static file and served its HTML fallback. WebAssembly streaming compile rejected the
  wrong MIME type, fell back to ArrayBuffer, and then ArrayBuffer instantiation failed because <!doctype html> isn't a valid wasm binary.

  Two-part fix:
  1. Missing file — tree-sitter.wasm is now in public/tree-sitter/ (consistent with how grammar wasm files are already handled). The buildStart hook in wasmMimePlugin also
  re-copies it on every build so it stays in sync with the installed web-tree-sitter version.
  2. MIME type — wasmMimePlugin adds a dev-server middleware that sets Content-Type: application/wasm for any .wasm request, enabling WebAssembly streaming compile instead of the
  slower ArrayBuffer fallback.
